  "text": "The Grafana datasource plugin query path is a multi-layered architecture that handles query requests from the UI to backend plugin execution and response transformation. Here is the complete flow:\n\n## 1. Query Request Handler (HTTP API Entry)\n\n**File: pkg/api/ds_query.go**\n- `QueryMetricsV2()` function at line 68 is the main HTTP handler for POST `/ds/query` requests\n- Routes between legacy query service and new API server based on `FlagQueryServiceRewrite` feature flag\n- `getDSQueryEndpoint()` at line 36 returns the appropriate handler (legacy or new)\n- `toJsonStreamingResponse()` at line 90 transforms backend responses to HTTP streaming JSON responses\n- Handles response code determination and error metadata (downstream status) \n\n## 2. Query Service (Core Query Processing)\n\n**File: pkg/services/query/query.go**\n- `ServiceImpl` type implements the main query processing logic\n- `QueryData()` method at line 126 processes standard queries\n- `QueryDataNew()` method at line 130 processes queries with per-query time ranges\n- `queryData()` at line 101 is the core implementation that:\n  - Parses metric requests via `parseMetricRequest()` at line 351\n  - Handles expressions via `handleExpressions()` at line 247\n  - Handles single datasources via `handleQuerySingleDatasource()` at line 288\n  - Executes concurrent queries via `executeConcurrentQueries()` at line 141\n- Related error types and models are in pkg/services/query/errors.go and pkg/services/query/models.go\n\n## 3. K8s API Server Query Handler\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/query/query.go**\n- `queryREST` type implements Kubernetes REST storage interface for queries\n- `Connect()` method at line 115 creates an HTTP handler for POST /apis/query.grafana.app/v0alpha1/namespaces/{ns}/query\n- `handleQuery()` function at line 244 processes the API server query requests by:\n  - Converting K8s API query format to legacy MetricRequest format\n  - Creating expression service with instance configuration\n  - Calling service.QueryData() from pkg/services/query\n- Returns transformed QueryDataResponse with proper HTTP status codes\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/query/register.go**\n- `QueryAPIBuilder` type orchestrates the query API server setup\n- Provides tracer, metrics, instance provider, and datasource lookup to query handlers\n- Registers the queryREST handler with the API server\n\n## 4. Plugin Query Dispatch (Backend Plugin Client)\n\n**File: pkg/plugins/manager/client/client.go**\n- `Service` type implements `plugins.Client` interface\n- `QueryData()` method at line 50 dispatches query requests to registered plugins\n- Handles plugin lookup from registry, error handling, and response frame processing\n\n**File: pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/grpc_plugin.go**\n- `grpcPlugin` type represents external gRPC plugins\n- `QueryData()` method at line 191 gets the plugin client and delegates the request\n- Handles plugin lifecycle (start/stop/decommission) and connection management\n\n**File: pkg/plugins/backendplugin/grpcplugin/client_v2.go**\n- `ClientV2` type implements gRPC client for plugins using plugin SDK protocol version 2\n- `QueryData()` method at line 162 converts query requests to protobuf, sends via gRPC, and converts responses back\n- Handles specific gRPC error codes (Unimplemented, Unavailable, ResourceExhausted)\n- Uses backend.ToProto() and backend.FromProto() for serialization\n\n**File: pkg/plugins/backendplugin/coreplugin/core_plugin.go**\n- `corePlugin` type represents built-in plugins (part of Grafana core)\n- `QueryData()` method at line 90 delegates to internal QueryDataHandler if available\n\n## 5. Datasource-Specific Query Handling\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/datasource/sub_query.go**\n- `subQueryREST` type handles queries to individual datasources via /apis/datasource.grafana.app/{uid}/query\n- `Connect()` method at line 60 creates handler that:\n  - Gets plugin context for the datasource\n  - Calls plugin client QueryData() with proper context\n  - Handles response error sources (downstream vs plugin errors)\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/datasource/queryconvert.go**\n- `queryConvertREST` type converts query formats between different datasources\n- Uses plugin `ConvertObjects()` method for format conversion\n- Handles query validation during conversion\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/datasource/querier.go**\n- `DefaultQuerier` type provides Query/Health/Resource methods\n- `Query()` method at line 74 delegates to the plugin client\n- Validates namespace context for datasource queries\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/datasource/register.go**\n- `DataSourceAPIBuilder` sets up the datasource API servers for individual plugins\n- Handles plugin client initialization and datasource context provision\n\n## 6. Query Service Client Builder\n\n**File: pkg/services/dsquerierclient/qs_datasource_client_builder.go**\n- `QSDatasourceClientBuilder` interface provides method to build query service clients\n- `QsDatasourceClientBuilderWithInstance` creates clients for multi-tenant query service flow\n- `BuildClient()` delegates to instance.GetDataSourceClient() for query service datasource clients\n\n**File: pkg/registry/apis/query/clientapi/clientapi.go**\n- `QueryDataClient` interface defines the contract for query service clients\n- `InstanceProvider` and `Instance` interfaces abstract query service configuration and datasource client creation\n\n## 7. Aggregator Plugin Handler\n\n**File: pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/query.go**\n- `QueryDataHandler()` at line 20 handles requests for aggregated query operations\n- Converts data.QueryDataRequest to backend.QueryDataRequest\n- Gets plugin context and calls client.QueryData()\n- Wraps response as aggregationv0alpha1.QueryDataResponse\n\n**File: pkg/aggregator/apiserver/plugin/handler.go**\n- `PluginHandler` type routes requests to appropriate handlers based on DataPlaneService spec\n- Registers /apis/{group}/{version}/namespaces/{ns}/datasources/{uid}/query route for query service\n\n## 8. Expression Service\n\n**File: pkg/expr/service.go**\n- `Service` type handles expression-based queries and transformations\n- `TransformData()` executes expression pipelines\n- `BuildPipeline()` and `ExecutePipeline()` orchestrate expression query execution\n- Integrates with datasource queries through dsquerierclient builder\n\n## Query Path Flow Summary\n\n1. **HTTP Request**: POST `/ds/query` arrives at QueryMetricsV2() in pkg/api/ds_query.go\n2. **Service Delegation**: Routes to hs.queryDataService.QueryData() or QueryDataNew()\n3. **Request Parsing**: QueryService parses queries, groups by datasource, identifies expressions\n4. **Single Datasource**: Calls handleQuerySingleDatasource() which builds plugin context and calls pluginClient.QueryData()\n5. **Plugin Dispatch**: Plugin client routes through registry to gRPC plugin or core plugin\n6. **gRPC Communication**: ClientV2.QueryData() converts to protobuf and communicates with external plugin\n7. **Response Transformation**: Responses converted back from protobuf to backend.QueryDataResponse\n8. **Expression Handling**: If expressions present, calls expressionService.TransformData() with datasource results\n9. **HTTP Response**: Final response streamed as JSON via toJsonStreamingResponse()\n\nThe new API server path (pkg/registry/apis/query/query.go) follows similar flow but through K8s REST handlers, enabling multi-tenant query service deployments."
